It’s really motivating to work with people who tell you some crazy idea and you think “that’ll never work”, and then a few weeks later they show you a PoC of it working perfectly

I guess the takeaway is: if an experienced researcher tells you something can’t be done, they probably have good reason for saying so based on their previous work. However, sometimes they’re totally wrong!

(One particular pitfall experienced researchers fall into I think is sometimes their understanding of a technology is often a bit dated and doesn’t exactly correspond to the current state, which might alter critical assumptions about the security model.)
